b'' b'dear folks:' b'' b"it's a pleasure to be able to announce the release of a new freeware program," b'xavier, an audio and video extension to interviews.' b'' b'xavier(extension av class for interviews) is a c++ class library' b'that adds multimedia capability to interviews. it allows composite' b'multimedia objects to be built from media objects.' b'' b'specifically, it adds audio and video objects to the classes available' b'in interviews and it does so without changing the' b'source code for the original classes (though several configuration' b'files for interviews need to be changed via a patch file).' b'' b'currently, the xavier audio classes are only supported on sun' b'workstations with an audio interface, such as the sparcstation2.' b'' b'xavier has been tested in the following environments:' b'' b'sun:' b'machine sparcserver470 sparcstation-ipc' b'os sun-os4.1.1 or later' b'c++ sun c++ ver2.1' b'' b'nec(ews):' b'machine ews4800/210,230' b'os ews-ux/v(rel4.0) wsos41 release5.1,release5.2' b'c++ c++ release3.1' b'' b'it can be obtained via anonymous ftp from' b'' b'interviews.stanford.edu in /pub/contrib/' b'(xavier.large-demo.tar, and xavier.tar)' b'' b'we are preparing a mailing-list for information regarding xavier.' b'if you are interested, please contact' b'' b'' b'i will add your e-mail address to our list.' b'' b'[reference]' b'o rei hamakawa, hizekazu sakagami, jun rekimoto:' b'audio and video extension to graphical interface toolkits,' b'the third international workshop on network and operating' b'system support for digital audio and video, san diego, b'' b'***********************************************************************' b'* b'* |o| b'* |o| c c systems research laboratories b'* |o| nec corporation b'* o| miyazaki 4-chome, tel b'* o| miyamae-ku, kawasaki, fax b'* o| kanagawa japan b'* b'***********************************************************************' 